<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="755" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119T&amp;M/7: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Special Mission at
                                        Lausanne</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-27T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            27, 1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>12. For Ambassador Child:</p>
                            <p>Mission’s 19 and 22, November 25, 3 p.m. and 25, 11 p.m. President
                                Harding and I strongly approve your statement which was timely and
                                appropriate.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
